summary: In this context, ethylbenzene is mentioned as one of several chemicals, including benzene, toluene, and xylene, that were obtained for experiments involving human tumor-derived cells. The focus is on the effects of these chemicals on cellular responses, particularly regarding heat shock protein (HSP) expression. Ethylbenzene is categorized alongside other volatile organic compounds (VOCs) but lacks a specific discussion of its unique interactions or effects compared to the other chemicals listed.
